<h4>Vertical alignment</h4>

<p>Vertical alignment refers to how text is positioned in relation to the top
 and bottom margins of the document. The default setting is "Top"ù and it 
works best for most documents. There are four settings you can choose from:</p>

<ul class="disc">
    <li><strong>Top</strong> - the text is positioned with the top margin</li>

    <li><strong>Center</strong> - the text is centered between the top and bottom margins</li>

    <li><strong>Justified</strong> - the text is centered between the top and bottom margins
evenly</li>

    <li><strong>Bottom</strong> - the text is positioned with the bottom margin</li>

</ul>

<p>You must find the Page Setup box in your version of Word.</p>

